messages.text: There's a man entering the building.
He'll be on the ninth floor in seven minutes.
I’m just a good Samaritan, trying to save your life.
How did you get my number?
It was right under “Idiots who ask stupid questions while their life is on the line.”
What about that black van outside your house?
It's been there for three weeks.
I…how did you know about that?
And sometimes you feel like you're being watched, right?
I see this guy sometimes. It’s almost like he's…
Look, I'll be glad to tell you my story just as soon as I'm done saving your life.
You have five minutes left, pal.
Oh, God. What should I do?
Should I call security? The police?
The police won't make it in time.
And security's been paid off to stay out of this.
The people trying to kill you.
Okay, now you’ve got me scared.
The man after you isn’t watching the stairs to the roof.
And he doesn't expect you to run.
You can give him the slip but you have to be quick about it.
Try not to look like you're running for your life.
Pretend you're just taking a private call and you don't want anyone listening.
They’ll let him know if they see anyone running.
Okay, I’m walking toward the roof.
l’ll pretend I’m talking to my fiancée.
I’ll bet she’s beautiful, isn’t she?
Uh, is this really the right time for this?
Hey, I'm just trying to keep your mind off the whole impending death thing.
As long as you don't have a nervous breakdown or something.
You need to work on your people skills.
And you need to work on your staying alive skills.
How close are you to the roof?
Do you know who's trying to kill me?
Okay, but who hired the hitman?
I don’t have any angry exes.
It could be anyone in your life.
Lots of people want to kill other people.
Now, could you do me a favor?
Could you stand on that big red X on the ground?
A man with a rifle appears on the roof of the building next door.
He aims it at Jimmy and shoots.
I just needed you on the roof to get a clear line of sight.
So I could get you out of the way once and for all.
Because maybe you didn’t have any angry exes.
